  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quality Control Manager (Mechanical)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n<p><br>\nThe role involves managing QC engineers, ensuring all ACMV and mechanical works meet project specifications, industry standards, and statutory requirements.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Lead and manage the QC (Mechanical) team to implement quality control processes for ACMV and mechanical works.</li>\n  <li>Review and approve quality procedures, inspection test plans (ITPs), and material submissions.</li>\n  <li>Oversee inspections, audits, and testing of equipment, materials, and site installations.</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with project specifications, codes, and safety regulations.</li>\n  <li>Manage non-conformance reports (NCRs), corrective actions, and follow-ups.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with clients, consultants, and subcontractors on quality matters.</li>\n  <li>Maintain accurate quality records, documentation, and reports for audits and project handover.</li>\n  <li>Provide technical guidance and mentoring to QC engineers and site personnel.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree/Diploma in Mechanical Engineering, Building Services, or related field.</li>\n  <li>Minimum 10 years of experience in quality control for ACMV/mechanical works, with at least 3 years in a managerial role.</li>\n  <li>Strong knowledge of ACMV and mechanical systems, materials, and QA/QC procedures.</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with Singapore codes, standards, and regulatory requirements.</li>\n  <li>Proven leadership and team management experience.</li>\n  <li>Strong problem-solving, analytical, and communication skills.</li>\n  <li>Experience in large-scale industrial or infrastructure projects is preferred.</li>\n  <li>Willingness to work at Tuas with transportation pick up at designated MRT station.</li>\n</ul>",
